This paper deals with the optimization of the placement of tethered UAVs for communication purposes. The problem involves considerations of signal path-loss, tether length, and hovering region, which are all related to networking and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques and mathematical modeling, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses safety considerations, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper proposes a closed-form solution for maximizing the line-of-sight probability, which is related to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
